<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
Story 4-3 T6 — synthetic-warning manifest (AC-7 negative case).

The <application> element intentionally declares android:allowBackup="true"
WITH tools:replace="android:allowBackup" — this overrides the plugin's
android:allowBackup="false" (which also has tools:replace) because the
consumer is the merge root and "last writer wins" when both sides assert
tools:replace.

Per AC-7 ("the plugin itself does not fail but the warning is visible"),
the merged manifest at build/intermediates/merged_manifest/release/
AndroidManifest.xml shows allowBackup="true". The
.github/workflows/manifest_merge_audit.yml::audit-warning job greps for
allowBackup="true", emits a ::warning:: annotation pointing at this file
+ line, and exits 0.

DO NOT remove android:allowBackup or tools:replace here — that would
collapse the AC-7 negative case into the AC-2 positive case (handled by
../synthetic-consumer/).
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools">
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:label="MwaSyntheticWarning"
        tools:replace="android:allowBackup" />
</manifest>
